Real estate can set you free
.
Step 1) Learn the skills needed to purchase your first real estate investment. There are many free resources out there walking you through the process step by step (YouTube)
.
Step 2) Accelerate your learning curve by self managing the real estate investment. You will make mistakes and potentially lose money in the short term, but overall, this will greatly strengthen your future decision-making 
.
Step 3) Learn and complete the renovation process and refinance your capital out of the asset.
.
Step 4) Have the discipline to avoid indulging in unnecessary personal expenses and vacations. 
You haven't made it yet. Great things take time
.
Step 5) Repeat the process with larger real estate assets each time and don't stop unless your cashflow 10x your yearly living expenses
.
.
